Tomato and Broccoli soup
- Canned tomatos
- Head of broccoli (1 head per can)
- Dried chilli flakes
- Rosemary? (not confident in this, but spice to taste)
- Salt to taste
- Chicken broth/ stock

Sourdough naan bread
- 50% flour 
- 50% water
- Olive Oil
- Salt
- flatten with hand
- Cool in skilet with oil

Daniela’s sauce
- 1 head of garlic
- 2 32 oz cans of crushed tomato (preferably bottles from Aurora or Unico. sometimes called Passata)
- 1 small can tomato paste
Spices: 
paprika 
olive oil 
oregano
rosemary
thyme
bayleaves
Salt
Black Pepper
Hot pepper (optional) (sriracha actually might be a cool add)

1. 1/4” of olive oil, onions on medium till browning. 
2. Tomato Passata, and spices heat to boil and let simmer. 

Sourdough bread
- Bubbly, active starter.
- test starter, if it floats it’s good. 
- Mix active starter with water, and flour at a 1:2:3 ratio, let this sit for a couple hours. 
- Dissolve 1 tablespoon of salt into half of the final amout of water to be used.
- slap and fold: work the dough until it’s smooth and doesn’t tear when you check it’s transparency. 
- Proofing: Shaping the dough in a bowl lined with cloth that is covered in flour.
- Shaping: fold the dough into a tight ball, letting the dough rest in between folds until you have a nice tight ball of dough. Once you are happy with the shape, let it sit in the fridge over night. 
- 20-21.5h Cooking: Preheat oven to 475F - 500F and bake bread for 1 - 1.5 hours. *If possible, steam helps to keep the break moist and springy.


Manchurian Gravy/ Sauce
- Olive Oil
- Garlic
- Green Chillies
- Green Onions
- Green peppers
- Corn flour and water (1:2 ratio)
- Soy Sauce
- Salt (To taste)
- Chilli garlic sauce

Directions
1. Finely dice everything.
2. Mess it up in a pan with oil
3. Allow everything to combine and soften together

Pakora
- Onion
- Garlic
- Cauliflower
- Flour (chickpea)

Directions
1. Combine spices in bowl and add water to make batter
2. Put cauliflower, onion and other veggies in batter
3. Fry in oil

Ginger Beef Sauce
- 2 Tbsp unseasoned rice vinegar
- 5 Tbsp soy sauce (use gluten-free soy sauce if cooking gluten-free)
- 1 Tbsp honey
- 1 Tbsp peeled, grated fresh ginger
- 1 teaspoon chile pepper flakes
- 1 teaspoon ground cumin
